description: Emotionally burned out over the destruction of "The American" squad and his subsequent "adventures", The American finds himself easy prey for a cultish "youth" organization operating in the desert outside Los Angeles. Who exactly is behind the bunch? Is The American's recruitment an accident--or part of some larger scheme? And to add an ambiguous twist, is it possible that The American is actually happier with his new life? Part one of a multi-part adventure (this storyline delayed from last issue to give the current "violence" storyline room to expand!).

THE PENULTIMATE ISSUE!

This is it! We arrived at the climax of the most universe-shattering event series in Top Cow history! We can’t tell you anything more! The final showdown you’ve been waiting for is here!
name: "Artifacts" part 12 of 13; "Origin: The Thirteenth"

description:
In the first story, Pete and Chat are in Greece because their school won an essay contest, and they get to visit a movie being filmed about Greek mythology. However, Magneto randomly shows up and attacks the Greek army, because he apparently thinks the Greek gods were mutants, and thus Greece would be a good headquarters for the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants.

Spidey tries to fight Magneto, but can't get past his shields. Another student has an idea to disrupt the magneto shield using electric wiring. Spidey dresses up as Zeus to hide the wiring, manages to disrupt the shield as planned, and knocks out Magneto.

In the second story, Spidey stops some bank robbers, but in the process a girl's ankle is broken. She and her friend are now heartbroken because they want to go to the Kylie Rogue concert (a teeny-bopper singer). Spidey promises to get Kylie's autograph to make up for her missing the concert. He breaks into the stadium and finds out that Kylie has been kidnapped and replaced by the Chameleon, who wants to steal the ticket sales.

Spidey tries to track down the Chameleon, knowing that he could have replaced the concert workers with his own thugs. He calls the girl with the broken ankle, and asks her for Kylie trivia so he knows which concert workers are on the Chameleon's payroll. He takes them out along with the Chameleon based on their wrong answers. Kylie brings the girl on stage during the concert to thank her.
name: Gods and Mutants!; Face Off

description:
The New All-Mothers of Asgardia battle their first threat to the Nine Realms!

Loki tries to expose the imposter thunder god Tanarus by enlisting the help of… Doctor Donald Blake?

Beyond the veil of space and time, the place where gods go to die is about to heat up…
name: The Mighty Tanarus: Part 2, The Walk

description: LAST ISSUE! The loving, affectionate parody of one of the greatest science fiction franchises of all time comes to its hilarious conclusion! In the tradition of ROBOT CHICKEN: STAR WARS and SPACEBALLS, follow Lady Leica and Al Alone on the run from Lord Salvador’s bumbling men as Jean-Luc Groundwalker faces his most harrowing task yet: daddy issues! Will Lady Leica ever find competent cohorts? Will Al Alone ever get over his namesake? Will Jean-Luc stop asking so many darn questions? Find out here, in the last chapter of the fan-pleasing romp that skewers one of the greatest adventure stories ever!
name: "It Was Still A Dark Time In The Kingdom..."

character_credits.name: Sir Gavin John Adams, Der Lord Barrister des Teufels

first_appearance_characters.name: Sir Gavin John Adams, Der Lord Barrister des Teufels

description: Hellboy joins forces with Batman and Starman in an adventure that takes them from the rooftops of Gotham to the steamy jungles of the Amazon, to rescue the first Starman, Ted Knight, from a secret Nazi organization that plans to use him to resurrect an elder god. Next, Hellboy travels to Arcadia in search of Ghost, a spectral vigilante caught up in a web of intrigue orchestrated by an ancient mask.
name: Masks and Monsters TPB

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: Mr. Spock faces a deadly choice as he tries to save the crew of a stranded shuttle! Featuring the likenesses of the new STAR TREK cast, this story boldly re-imagines a classic episode, The Galileo Seven, but in the new timeline of the hit movie!
name: The Galileo Seven, Part 2

description: Fright-master Steve Niles continues his all-new 30 DAYS OF NIGHT ongoing series, with warped genius Sam Kieth (creator of The Maxx) joining in the bloodletting! Our curious heroine is granted her greatest wish, but will it also be her last? Features an all-new cast of characters being introduced to the world of 30 DAYS OF NIGHT for the first time!

Monocyte begins his death march towards the Olignostic city, fending off relentless attacks on his journey to destroy their immortality machinery. Meanwhile, a powerless Olignostic seizes on Monocyte’s appearance to acquire power. Art by menton3 (ZvR: Aventure) with a covers by Riley Rossmo (Proof), an incentive cover by the legendary Bill Sienkiewicz (Elektra: Assassin), and side stories by superstar Ben Templesmith and newcomers Alan Hubbard and Chris Newman.

How do you measure evil? Hell-bent on destroying everything in his path, and fuming from his latest setback, Eric makes a decision that will push him past the point of no return. Explore your dark side.

BOOK THIRTY-FIVE: THE MAXIMUM SECRET

Nothing you could possibly imagine is about to occur in the pages of this comic book! Multiply your expectations by a thousand, and you still wouldn’t come close! As the end draws near, Commander Adam Archer and company are forced to confront everything they ever believed in… But what sacrifices will they make to ensure the evolutionary process?

GØDLAND PUTS YOUR BRAIN BETWEEN A ROCK AND A HARD PLACE!
name: The Maximum Secret

description: Stygia: mysterious land of black magics, serpent gods, and deadly intrigues…and the last place in the Hyborian Kingdoms a sane person would venture. But with Emperor Strabonus' assassins hot on her heels, and accounts to settle in Stygia, that's just where Red Sonja is headed.
name: Echoes of War, Part 1 - Through Stygian Sands

description:
This collects short stories on The Phantom in prose format both in hardcover and softcover.

This book has the first team-up ever of The Phantom and the Green Hornet, and a brand-new story written by Harlan Ellison.

To the outside world, this man, seemingly immortal, has always worn the mask. As the legend grew, it transcended the life of any one mortal. And that legend became The Phantom.

This book has a special feature - introduction by Phantom creator Lee Falk's daughter, Diane Falk.
name: The Phantom Chronicles

description: The Phantom Prose anthology that came as softcover, hardcover and also a limited plus edition that contained a special chapbook.

The Chapbook originally came with the first plus issue of the volume: The Phantom Chronicles. This is a very rare 6" x 9" color cover saddle-stiched book that shows the art that was not used for the Chronicles earlier. It also features insights and liner notes from artist Rubén Procopio. The interiors of the chapbook are black and white on manilla stock, 28pgs.

These came out in a very limited numbers. They were also sold by Moonstone separately for a short period.
name: The Phantom Chronicles Artist's Annex
